The paper describes a deep learning approach for automated lumbar spinal stenosis grading using natural language processing and image data. This involves accurate vertebral segmentation and disc-level localization, as well as a multi-input, multi-task, and multi-class convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Deep learning (cs.DL) is also a likely sub-category given the methodology used. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is less likely but still possible, as the paper involves extracting information from free-text radiology reports.
